            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p>Stranger Things is a critically acclaimed science fiction horror series created by the Duffer Brothers and released on Netflix. Set in the 1980s in the small town of Hawkins, Indiana, the show follows a group of kids who uncover government experiments, supernatural forces, and a parallel dimension called the Upside Down after their friend Will Byers mysteriously disappears.</p>

            <p>The series introduces Eleven, a girl with telekinetic abilities, who escapes from a secret government lab and helps Will’s friends battle terrifying creatures like the Demogorgon and Mind Flayer. As the seasons progress, the group faces new monsters, government conspiracies, and personal struggles, all while trying to protect their town from supernatural threats.</p>

            <p>With its mix of thrilling suspense, 1980s nostalgia, emotional storytelling, and strong character development, Stranger Things has become a global pop culture phenomenon. The show has received critical acclaim, numerous awards, and a massive fan following, making it one of Netflix’s most successful original series.</p>

